{#
  ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  The grid is driven by content/photography/photography.json. JSON can't hold
  comments, so the reference shape lives here (it never renders). Drop image
  files into content/img/photography/, then list each one.

  Fields per entry:
    Required:  src  — image URL; served from /img/photography/
               alt  — alt text for accessibility

  Any image size works — the grid arranges them automatically; images load lazily.

  Reference shape:

      [
        {
          "src": "/img/photography/my-photo.webp",
          "alt": "Description of the photo"
        }
      ]
  ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#}
<h1 class="page-title">Photography</h1>
<div class="photo-grid">
  {% for p in photography %}
  <img class="photo" src="{{ p.src }}" alt="{{ p.alt }}" loading="lazy" />
  {% endfor %}
</div>
